title: Lines in conics

If a [[conic|Projective conic]] $$Q$$ contains three points on a line $$l$$, then:

* $$Q$$ contains the whole line,
* the corresponding quadratic form is degenerate and
* the conic $$Q$$ is either the line $$l$$ or the union of $$l$$ with another line.